Name: Paul Feldman
Attribute: Run into issues with HB 2201 or need to elaborate?
Value:
Here's my comment:
I am following the lead of Front and Centered, Environmental Justice Council, Sierra Club, Washington Conservation Action, The Nature Conservancy, and 350. It would be premature to make more than the necessary technical changes to allow continued investigation of the effects of linkage on Washington's allowance market. We must delay final analysis of linkage impact on allowance prices and revenue streams until after CARB completes its current work on changes to the CA program. The final analysis must include questions of impact on Washington's allowance prices, allowance market, and projected revenue. Any final linkage agreement must keep offsets below the cap and does not restrict the number of offsets on tribal lands.
